<title>BELGIUM: BELGIAN CAMPINE H1 1996 PROFIT PLUNGES.</title>
<headline>BELGIAN CAMPINE H1 1996 PROFIT PLUNGES.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months to June 30</p>
<p>(in millions of Belgian francs unless stated)</p>
<p>    Non-cons net profit	   6.6 vs   42.3</p>
<p>    Non-cons cash flow	   32.0 vs   79.0</p>
<p>    Non-cons EPS (francs)	  44 vs    282</p>
<p>    Non-cons turnover	   773.0 vs  865.0</p>
<p>    Non-cons current	     14.0 vs   53.8</p>
<p>    Exceptional loss		8.0 vs    0.0</p>
<p>NOTE - Belgian lead and antimony producer Campine NV, which also recycles waste containing lead, said turnover dropped 10.6 percent mainly due to lower antimony oxide prices.</p>
<p>It said it expected full-year 1996 non-consolidated profit to be lower than that of 1995. It added it also expected a weak 1996 consolidated result.</p>
